author: Doug Knoop
title: ‘Brooklyn Nine-Nine” rolls out Halloween-themed episode
text:
‘Brooklyn Nine-Nine’ There should be an extra bit of fun on tonight’s Halloween-themed episode of this police comedy (for those who haven’t seen it, it’s reminiscent of “Barney Miller” — if you’re under 30, look it up). Jake Peralta (goofy Andy Samberg) and Ray Holt (beautifully deadpan Andre Braugher) compete for the title of “amazing detective slash genius”). 8:30 p.m. Sunday, Oct. 25, on Fox.

Doug Knoop: dknoop@seattletimes.com or on Twitter @dougknoop 

Also on Sunday Most Read Stories Seattle principal losing his job over unfinished teacher evaluations Seattle Seahawks' Kam Chancellor takes to Twitter to protest fine from NFL 5 ways CaliBurger is better than In-N-Out Seattle Mariners manager Scott Servais may not be a sexy hire, but is he the right one? Sports on TV & radio Unlimited Digital Access. $1 for 4 weeks. “MLS Soccer,” 4 p.m. (KZJO): Real Salt Lake at Seattle Sounders FC (Live).
“Madam Secretary,” 8 p.m. (CBS): When Elizabeth disagrees with the president’s response to tension with Russia, she is pushed out of the inner circle; incriminating photos of Harrison and Stevie come to light.
“The Walking Dead,” 9 p.m. (AMC): A small group, including Rick, runs into hurdles while trying to return to Alexandria, and some may not make it back.
“The Leftovers,” 9 p.m. (HBO): Nora awakens in the midst of an earthquake to find Kevin missing; the Murphys are left reeling after Evie’s disappearance; Kevin returns home with no memory of the night before; an old enemy returns.
“The Guilty,” 10 p.m. (KCTS): DCI Maggie Brand investigates a five-year-old case involving a boy who disappeared during a neighborhood cookout.
“Quantico,” 10:01 p.m. (ABC): Alex and Ryan get close when the trainees leave campus for their first undercover assignment; Alex tells her side of the story in a public interview.
